	(text "NOTES\n- EQ: set to minimum/near-minimum for short traces (<25mm). Overdriving EQ on short traces amplifies noise.\n- Config resistor values: select from DS100BR111 datasheet table before PCB spin.\n- All 100nF bypass caps: 0603 ceramic, place as close to VCC pins as possible.\n- All high speed data coupling caps: 0402 ceramic, placed within 2mm of DS100BR111 pins\n- LDO output cap: 10uF minimum required for LD1117 stability.\n- TX_DISABLE: driven by MCP2221A GP3 (active HIGH disables laser).\n- I2C: 100kHz per SFP+ MSA spec. Check clock stretching if module unresponsive."
		(exclude_from_sim no)
		(at 15.24 186.69 0)
		(effects
			(font
				(size 1.27 1.27)
			)
			(justify left)
		)
		(uuid "eac3a259-3790-42eb-9b29-9ab71e3f760f")
	)
	(text "NET CLASSES (via directive label rectangles)\n\nUSB3_SS  0.2mm trace, 0.2mm diff gap, 0.2mm clearance (100R diff)\n  SSTX+, SSTX-, SSRX+, SSRX-\n\nUSB2  0.2mm trace, 0.15mm diff gap, 0.15mm clearance (90R diff)\n  D+, D-, D+_2, D-_2, D+_3, D-_3\n\nPower  0.5mm trace, 0.8mm via, 0.2mm clearance\n  VBUS, VBUS_2, VBUS_3, +3.3V, VUSB, GND\n\nDefault  0.2mm trace, 0.2mm clearance\n  I2C (SDA, SCL), GPIO, TX_DIS_MCU, RX_LOS_MCU"
		(exclude_from_sim no)
		(at 13.716 26.67 0)
		(effects
			(font
				(size 1.27 1.27)
			)
			(justify left)
		)
		(uuid "f7b25ddc-a3a4-4904-9ff4-599b2ebcb800")
	)
